Troops of 1 Division Nigerian Army on Wednesday at about 0430 hours raided a bandits hideout at Conan Bature East of Rijana and Kasarami Farms house in Chikun Local Government Area of Kaduna and killed two bandits and recovered weapons. The Acting Director Army Public Relations Col Sagir Musa in a statement said the raid followed credible intelligence from a good Samaritan that the abandoned Kasarami farm house was reportedly forcefully occupied by criminals and had been used as a shelter and a place where victims of kidnapping were kept. He said “during the raid operation, contact was made with the hoodlums with fierce exchange of fire that led to the extermination of two bandits.” Items recovered include; two AK 47 Rifles, two AK 47 Magazines, 51 rounds of 7.62 mm Special ammunition and two techno cell phone. He noted that the Nigerian Army is ever committed and determined to protecting life and property of all Nigerians, and thanked the good Samaritan for providing the information that resulted in the successful raid operation. He further called for more support from citizens in order to checkmate terrorism, banditry and other sundry crimes in Nigeria.